SELECT r.first_name, r.last_name, hm.model_name, gd.analysis_result FROM researchers r JOIN healthcare_models hm ON r.researcher_id = hm.researcher_id JOIN genetic_data gd ON hm.data_id = gd.data_id WHERE gd.genetic_sequence LIKE '%AGTC%' ORDER BY hm.model_name ASC;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT r.researcher_id) AS unique_researchers, COUNT(hm.model_id) AS total_models FROM researchers r LEFT JOIN healthcare_models hm ON r.researcher_id = hm.researcher_id GROUP BY r.department HAVING total_models > 0 ORDER BY unique_researchers DESC;
